Sentencas: A series of cyclic voltammetry, chronoamperometry and electrochemical impedance experiments have been carried out in order to investigate the effect of cathode composition and porosity on the electrochemical characteristics of strontium-doped lanthanum, praseodymium and gadolinium cobaltite cathodes.
Titulo: Electrochemical and gas phase parameters of cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The impedance responses at different electrode potentials of the half cell and symmetric single cell setups are compared and analyzed by the equivalent circuit modeling method.
Titulo: Electrochemical and gas phase parameters of cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The deconvolution of impedance spectra for single cell cathode and anode reactions contributions based on the results of simultaneous analysis of half cells and symmetric single cells has been made by differential impedance real part vs. ac frequency plot analysis method.
Titulo: Electrochemical and gas phase parameters of cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Noticeable influence of cathode chemical composition, meso-porosiiy and macro-porosity on the electrochemical activity of the oxygen electroreduction has been demonstrated.
Titulo: Electrochemical and gas phase parameters of cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Seeming activation energy values have been calculated and discussed.
Titulo: Electrochemical and gas phase parameters of cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
